  "text": "Holter data evaluated included the following: heart rate, atrial ectopy, ventricular ectopy, supraventricular tachycardia, atrioventricular block, symptoms, and whether specific symptoms correlated with a rhythm disturbance. Atrial and ventricular ectopy were subclassified to rare/occasional (<720 ectopic beats over 24 hours), frequent (>720 ectopic beats over 24 hours), couplets/triplets (2-3 beats in a row), nonsustained tachycardia (4-30 beats in a row), and sustained tachycardia (>30 beats in a row). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Significant",
